  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How long does it take to open a savings bank account in ICICI bank?",
  "response": "The time it takes to open a savings account with ICICI Bank can vary based on several factors, including the method of application and the completeness of your documentation. Here\u2019s a general guideline:\n\n1. **Online Application:**\n   - If you apply online through ICICI Bank's website or mobile app, the process can be relatively quick. You'll need to fill out the application form, upload the necessary documents, and complete the video KYC (Know Your Customer) verification.\n   - The entire online process might take around 15-30 minutes to complete the application. However, the account activation can take a few business days, depending on the verification process.\n\n2. **In-Branch Application:**\n   - Visiting a branch in person can take longer due to waiting times and the need for face-to-face interaction. The process typically involves filling out forms, submitting documents, and completing the KYC verification.\n   - The entire process at the branch might take around 30-60 minutes, depending on the branch's busyness and the completeness of your documentation. Account activation can still take a few business days.\n\n3. **Documentation and Verification:**\n   - Ensure you have all required documents ready, such as proof of identity, proof of address, and recent photographs. Missing documents can delay the process.\n   - The bank will need to verify your details, which can take 1-3 business days.\n\nIn summary, the application process itself can take anywhere from 15 minutes to an hour, but the account activation might take an additional 1-3 business days. Always check with the bank for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
